    "long_instructions": "# Do This:\r\n1. Add print statements to print out each variable.\r\n    - *Hint: What do you need to do to combine non-string variables (like `num_skateboards`) with strings in a `print()` statement?*\r\n2. Manda just got a new skateboard! Update the `num_skateboards` variable to reflect Manda getting a new skateboard using an arithmetic operator (`+`, `-`, `*`, `/`).\r\n3. Print the updated total.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n#### AI Tutor Support\r\n\r\n::: details [**Not sure how to print variables?**]\r\nAsk AI:\r\n- Why does my print statement give an error when I include a number?\r\n- How do I print text and a variable together?\r\n:::\r\n\r\n::: details [**Stuck on updating the variable?**]\r\nAsk AI:\r\n- How do I increase a variable’s value in Python?\r\n- What happens if I use `num_skateboards + 1` without assigning it back to the variable?\r\n\r\n:::\r\n"
